i want to go far away.

Fairweather Motion Sickness lyrics

Ever feel like there's so much more to life
But you just have no clue how to reach it right now?
Sick of all the talk between friends
All the things that offend
Desire everything to be set straight but we can't go back in time
Please don't leave without saying goodbye to me
It's only me running after you 'cause you're everything I need
Sour spirit mixed with the autumn disposition
Never looking out farther than my own room I tell myself I'll forget you.
I know that's not true
I just hate to be around when things break down between us
And all the times we spent together.
All the nights we screamed.
I cant remember what its like to feel alright.
I can't let go of what's killing me.
So this is my apology to you.
I hope you know I love you.
Lets put back together the world we built between us.
I'm sorry.

♥ Happy 91st Birthday Frank Sinatra ♥

come gather 'round people
wherever you roam
and admit that the waters
around you have grown
and accept it that soon
you'll be drenched to the bone.
If your time to you
Is worth savin'
then you better start swimmin'
or you'll sink like a stone
for the times they are a-changin'.

come writers and critics
who prophesize with your pen
and keep your eyes wide
the chance won't come again
and don't speak too soon
for the wheel's still in spin
and there's no tellin' who
that it's namin'.
for the loser now
will be later to win
for the times they are a-changin'.

come senators, congressmen
please heed the call
don't stand in the doorway
don't block up the hall
for he that gets hurt
will be he who has stalled
there's a battle outside
and it is ragin'.
it'll soon shake your windows
and rattle your walls
for the times they are a-changin'.

come mothers and fathers
throughout the land
and don't criticize
what you can't understand
your sons and your daughters
are beyond your command
your old road is
rapidly agin'.
please get out of the new one
if you can't lend your hand
for the times they are a-changin'.

the line it is drawn
the curse it is cast
the slow one now
will later be fast
as the present now
will later be past
the order is
rapidly fadin'.
and the first one now
will later be last
For the times they are a-changin'

okay so i'm not aloud to get my belly button pierced til im 18 or if i get a B+ in every class for the two first marking periods, so yeah when i turn 18. things are so much different than last summer. well, for one thing tara isn't living here ha. and im not drinking every day, which is a good thing caus thats lame. and plus you gain a lot of weight if you are constantly consuming alcohol, which explains my extra pounds i put on last summer. hmm, what else... no summer art this year, which is sad. but i do have a job, so that's new. i like having a schedule and a consistent pay. my friends are basically the same, give or take a few. but having new people hang out with my group is always fun. i personally have been remaining drama-free, and it's so nice. i hope that lasts throughout the summer. prolly not. the hills is on in a half hour holla at that. this is the first night that i haven't been out since the begining of the summer, so its nice to have a break and just chill.

wow tonight was sooo amazing. went out to dinner for my bday with my family at "the pub" but then my dad pulled up at the hilton and i was like "?" and we went in. and omg. it was a rat pack show. rat pack impersonators. oh emmm geee. there was about 200 people there and all of them were old! haha i was the youngest person there and i loved it! anyway, first we had dinner and then the boys came out on stage and sung a few songs seperately and then together and then they did a few of their skits. then there was a intermission and i got my picture taken with them. then the show continued and frank dedicated a song to me and sung it to me the whole time. afhds9phpsa. and then later on he called me up because it was my birthday and i danced with them on stage. soo goood. it was the best birthday present everrr<333 thank you mother and father. i love you

okay so monday was the worst day ever. but tuesday was the best day ever. haha life is weird. anyway, things are good at the moment. the s test can suck it. i hated the math section but i actually enjoy writing so the was easy. i haven't had much time lately. babysitting for long hours ehhh. i went to the library and got some books on Hawaii and i got a movie too! and i watched like half of it. i kinda knew everything in it from reading the books. i'm so excited. caus it will be amazing. and every time i feel like shit or something bad happens in the next 7 years, i can just think about moving to Hawaii and it will make me feel better. this week was odd. i thought it was wednesday for two days in a row and i thought today was friday.thats about it. and pyce dewaele.

today was completely horrible. i felt like crying every other period. and punching every other person in the face. things aren't good in the fam. it makes me depressed and sad and worried. i hate violence. i hate the schools bus policies. and i hate cancer. all i've been doing lately is blocking out all of the shit going on, putting it aside, then denying it all together. reality sucks. it makes me happy when i think about hawaii. i'm getting serious about this. i wish i could go right now.

I'm moving to Hawaii when I'm 24.A year after college, i will find work in the city of Honolulu most likely in the field of computers/graphic design.I'm not sure whether i'll live on Oahu, (the island where Honolulu is located)but i'll probably end up living there at first instead of Molokai- where i really would like to live becuase it is the most undeveloped island of Hawaii and there is barely anyone there. There's rainforrests and desserted beaches there.and there isn't even one single traffic light there. the only problem is, it is about 50 miles east of Oahu. Which would be extremely expensive to fly back and fourth every day. I could live outside of Honolulu for my first few years, and then once the money starts rollin'in, i will save up for a speed boat to take me to and from work, so i can then live on Molokai Island. You're probably all laughing reading this now, and I don't blame you because i've had a lot of krazy/stupid ideas in the past, which you may be aware of, and i am only 16 and may not know so much. but i have seven years to figure this out, and it will be a dream come true. and tara hates me right now, but she'll be happy in 7 years when she visits me and takes her pick from all the hawaiian guys that i plan to hook her up with.
I'm very excited about this.
And no, it is not impossible.

time to update. for once....um,i woke up with a krazy fever. i had the most fucked up scary dream ever. i dont even wanna talk about it ha. just made some spaghetti. chances of being grounded=50/50. hmmm. so whatev. tomorrow will mark a full 2 months without cutting my hair. i'm proud of myself. um, yesterday i did three of my six hours w/ chiaro. it was actually pretty okay. i did good. cept, when i swerved caus there was a hairy spider on my window. oh god. that was horrible. haha anyway, i get my permit tomorrow holla! and then my license on October 13, 2006 ;) i'm pumped for october. my hair will be all longish, i'll be skinnier, and it'll halloween and i'll fucking have my license! wooo. i was cleaning out my room today. and i have ten dollars! and i found my RIP the june spirit shirt that i made from seventh grade. wow i was a nerd. haha. i can't wait til my sister comes home, so i can drive with her.

1. you are the best friend that i ever had. i honestly don't know what i'd do without you. i can't even imagine life without you.haha eww, but true. you know me better than anyone else does. when we're together, we're like one person,that was split up into two bodies..haha? it seems like we've been friends forever, when its only been three something years. i have the most amazing memories with you. i spend the most time with you. i love you. and im so excited caus i know we're gonna be best friends fo' lyfe, but fo' real. think about that. it's really exciting =) bfffl! ♥ 2. it feels so fucking good to have ya back.this school year has been so amazing so far with you. i'm so glad we got to be closer than close. we've had a lot of fun/krazy/scary/interesting memories together this year. i love ittt and i love you. and this summer's gonna be fucking awesome. and yeah, we will have plenty of "off the wall" sleepovers if you know what im sayin' ;) love ya 3. at this point, our friendship is pretty much unstopable. i mean, we've been friends for fuckin 4,5 years? yeah. thats right. and we're still goin' strong. |so basically, i love you, and i'll be there for you always, no matter what. love youuuuuu 4. yo, i love you. without you, my life would be a 1000 times duller.you keep things entertaining and you spice things up. thats what i like about you. well, i love you. we've gotten so close since the begining of last summer. you're one of my best friends. i feel like you'll always be there for me. and i will always be there for you. love ya cuzzie. 5. you're so fucking hot, and i can't take it! 6. i haven't seen you two in like fucking 2 or 3 months. thats so ridickk. hang out, real soon. caus i miss you girls ;) 7. i actually though you were kool. i was so wrong. 8. yes, i still hate you. no, i don't wanna be friends again. 9. we're growing apart. i guess that happens sometimes. 10. you're so cute. you're like the perfect boy. i wish i could tell you that, without it being incredibly awkward. 11. you're like my ro-model. i will never really admit to that. but some have noticed.but that's your job.its basically always been like that, but recently, its gotten worse.haha.i tend to talk like you, dress like you, and act like you now.i really miss you, even when i don't see you for just one week-end. we've been getting along a lot better lately.i guess b/c we're both getting older, although we still fight here and there, which is quite alright. you have always been there for me. and i mean, since day 1. meaning my d.o.b. it's good to know that you and i will be there for eachother always, even though we don't have a choice, since we're blood. anyway, i love you and thanks for...well thanks for everything. 12. i wish we talked more this year, b/c its weird not talking to you. its all interesting talking to you, whether its about whats currently going on in your life or we're just rambling about some past memories we've had together. i'm really scared that we'll lose touch when we get older and i hope that never happens. i know you're goin through some tough stuff right now, and i just want you to know,that i love you and that i will always be there for you. always. if you ever need to talk or just need some company,i'll be there. i miss you. my blood.

"blindfolded" - Saves the Day

So now I've made the decision 
to walk behind you in the dark for the rest of my life 
and I'll never show my face again 
because it's too scarred and bloody to be enough 
and I don't have the right stuff- 
all I have are the empty boxes to carry away your heart 
and I think that tonight I will sneak into your house 
and I'll sing songs and wake you up 
and I'll take you blindfolded dancing onto bridges 
and you'll say you don't to be with me 
caus' no one ever does and no one ever thinks of me that way 
but I will even drive you home if you never let me forget about you 
and if you promise me that I'm good enough for someone 
caus' I've got to be good enough for you 
and someday soon I'll get it right 
and then you'll see just how good I can be 
so don't ask me about forever because right now I'm feeling lost 
but there's got to be some place for me because
if there isn't where will I go? 
Will there be some place for me and will you be there waiting?
Will you be there waiting for me? 
If and when we get there please catch me before I crawl all the way home 
but I won't stop until you do.
